🟦 BLUE PATH | “I’m Fine” Doesn’t Always Mean Fine
🧭 For Pitch 1-Pager – Overview of the Blue Path in the Guidepost App
🔹 User Enters With…
“I’m fine.”
“I’m okay.”
“I don’t really know how I feel.”
They may seem emotionally stable, but are often disconnected, numb, or masking. This user is functioning, but there’s a mismatch between how they’re acting and how they actually feel.
🔹 Core Goal of the Blue Path
To help users gently check beneath the surface and identify if “fine” is actually… foggy, fatigued, or emotionally misaligned.
This path uses subtle check-ins, body-based awareness, and calming tone to help them reconnect without pressure.
🔹 Tone of Voice
🧊 Chill, observant, emotionally fluent.
Never pushy. Juniper meets them with curiosity, calm, and zero “fix-it” energy.
🔹 Transformation Arc
From 🤷 "I’m just coasting" → 🌀 "I actually feel kind of off" → 🌱 "Here’s one small thing I can do or name today."
The path helps users either gently re-engage with their needs or shift into a more aligned path (Red, Yellow, or Green) once clarity emerges.
🔹 6-Stage Flow
1. Surface Scan – Checks if “fine” is real or a placeholder
2. Subtle Signals Check – Mood-matching or sensory metaphor options
3. Mismatch Moment – Explores disconnects between body, head, and emotion
4. Quiet Needspotting – Offers the 🧰 Micro-Needs Menu
5. Reorientation – Suggests one small action, rest, or focus anchor
6. Gentle Closure or Re-entry – Affirms awareness, offers path shift or calm close
🔹 Embedded Tools
📦 Mood-Matching Visual
🧰 Micro-Needs Menu
⚙️ Gentle Focus Anchor
⚙️ Start Small Planner
✨ Mini Reflection Tags
🔹 Shift Options Built In
🔁 From Blue →
🟡 Yellow (Stuck but thinking ahead)
🟢 Green (Ready to focus)
🔴 Red (Overwhelmed underneath)
